<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 07 at 1:42PM MDT until July 07 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 230 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN GLACIER COUNTY...
At 142 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles north of
North Browning, or 35 miles west of Cut Bank, moving northeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Glacier County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
